cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper heavily relies on Prolog, a logic programming language, to provide executable specifications of mathematical objects. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Prolog as a flexible meta-language. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with rooted ordered trees and binary trees. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses balanced parenthesis languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the efficiency of arithmetic operations performed with symbolic objects.
